1
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:10,000
[Episode 24: 0.01% Probability]

2
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,959
<i>I've always been like this,</i>

3
00:01:19,959 --> 00:01:22,036
<i>staring at your back from afar,</i>

4
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:24,150
<i>from age 8,</i>

5
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:26,840
<i>through 18,</i>

6
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:28,112
<i>to 28.</i>

7
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:30,560
<i>I know you're vain,</i>

8
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,040
<i>willful,</i>

9
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:34,200
<i>careless of the consequences,</i>

10
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,920
<i>and despicable</i>

11
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:38,520
<i>someone I shall keep my distance from.</i>

12
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:39,784
But...

13
00:01:40,444 --> 00:01:42,480
You're driving me crazy!

14
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,257
Mom, I don't know her.

15
00:01:44,257 --> 00:01:46,599
With such a crowd,
it'll be embarrassing if it gets out of hand.

16
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:48,480
You count the stupid beans every time.

17
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,040
Aren't you embarrassed?

18
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,560
If I don't do that,

19
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:53,760
how can I scare those girls away?

20
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:54,947
You...

21
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:01,287
Ren Xi Zhou, are you an idiot?

22
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,683
Is this an improvisation of Mr. Lu?

23
00:02:09,683 --> 00:02:11,712
Probably... not.

24
00:02:11,712 --> 00:02:12,834
The plan!

25
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,840
I'll ask the planner.

26
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,278
Call the security.

27
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:28,697
Run!

28
00:02:33,646 --> 00:02:35,720
Mom, it must be your red underwear

29
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,759
that scared them away.

30
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:38,141
Shut up!

31
00:02:38,141 --> 00:02:40,375
- Security! Security!
- Alright, alright.

32
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:43,074
But you're so unreasonable,

33
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:45,800
like the summer night tide

34
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,160
washing over my isolated isle.

35
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:50,760
Even if the unknown

36
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:52,240
is terrifying.

37
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,903
I'll dive...

38
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,170
into the deep ocean...

39
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:02,435
time and again.

40
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,846
We played it together.

41
00:03:20,424 --> 00:03:21,520
<i>The three-legged race?</i>

42
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,626
<i>No.</i>

43
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,482
<i>Who'd play the three-legged race with you?</i>

44
00:03:25,482 --> 00:03:27,040
<i>By chance.</i>

45
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,680
We have a 0.01% probability.

46
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,780
You're not unlucky at all.

47
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,241
Please, Mr. Drizzle.

48
00:03:47,832 --> 00:03:49,479
You're out of your mind

49
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:50,920
to marry in place of Li Nan Xi.

50
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:52,769
Have you thought about the consequences?

51
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,600
My hand hurts from carrying a bag.

52
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,887
I need to change a hand.

53
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:02,439
You have time to carry a bag?

54
00:04:02,439 --> 00:04:03,840
Sure. It's real.

55
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,280
Can you not do this?

56
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,960
What's up, my Highness?

57
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,960
When someone approaches you bravely,

58
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,480
you drive him away with your vanity.

59
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,720
If you regret it,

60
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,444
you can let go at any time.

61
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:21,620
What logic is this?

62
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:23,600
What do you mean by logic?

63
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,560
Since our reunion,

64
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,199
I advance while you retreat,

65
00:04:27,199 --> 00:04:28,800
and I retreat while you advance.

66
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,480
It's like a dance.

67
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,640
I know you're a sly partner,

68
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,800
but I have to finish it with you.

69
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,720
What logic is this?

70
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,034
I don't know.

71
00:04:43,439 --> 00:04:45,160
I can't let go.

72
00:04:48,526 --> 00:04:50,000
But you can let me go.

73
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,267
Never.

74
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:55,360
Your letters were sent

75
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:57,280
to a student apartment.

76
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:00,207
I contacted the apartment manager

77
00:05:00,207 --> 00:05:01,279
and paid him

78
00:05:01,279 --> 00:05:03,120
to find an international logistics company,

79
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,879
to ship all the letters addressed

80
00:05:04,879 --> 00:05:05,920
to Ren Xi Zhou.

81
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:08,482
Do you know how much it cost?

82
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,200
But these letters aren't mine.

83
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,680
Mine.

84
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,120
My replies

85
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,461
to each of your letters.

86
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,319
<i>It just rained.</i>

87
00:05:32,319 --> 00:05:34,040
<i>The hydrangeas bloom,</i>

88
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,240
<i>purple and lively.</i>

89
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:38,000
<i>I bought red yarn.</i>

90
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,160
<i>I want to knit a scarf.</i>

91
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:42,680
<i>You should come to see the sunset here.</i>

92
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:45,000
<i>Peeked through the crack,</i>

93
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,399
<i>it's still golden and gorgeous.</i>

94
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:49,360
<i>I met a stray orange cat,</i>

95
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,090
<i>smooth and sleek.</i>

96
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:55,120
It's written that

97
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,760
the rainy season is over,

98
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,644
and it's sunny every day.

99
00:06:00,352 --> 00:06:01,990
Have you ever aired a quilt?

100
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,237
Why?

101
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,922
I enjoy writing nonsense.

102
00:06:14,319 --> 00:06:17,208
"I like the smell of a sun-warmed quilt."

103
00:06:17,959 --> 00:06:20,384
Must you read it?

104
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:24,125
My tenosynovitis acted up from writing.

105
00:06:25,399 --> 00:06:27,046
You want me to let you go?

106
00:06:27,046 --> 00:06:28,120
Impossible!

107
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,480
Never!

108
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,316
I've always...

109
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,600
liked you.

110
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,120
No more distance?

111
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,345
Yes.

112
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,780
Have you ever kissed?

113
00:06:59,759 --> 00:07:01,487
Written a kissing scene?

114
00:07:15,959 --> 00:07:17,472
They're here!

115
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:31,465
I removed it for you.

116
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,488
Thank you.

117
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,520
Here.

118
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:40,820
Wait for me.

119
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,218
Dad.

120
00:08:08,218 --> 00:08:09,720
<i>Li Nan Xi.</i>

121
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,464
<i>Is it so hard to settle down and get married?</i>

122
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,720
I dislike him.

123
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:19,311
<i>I truly spoiled you.</i>

124
00:08:19,311 --> 00:08:21,235
<i>Who told you you could
refuse anything you dislike?</i>

125
00:08:21,235 --> 00:08:22,279
<i>Come back now.</i>

126
00:08:22,279 --> 00:08:24,399
<i>Or you're not my daughter.</i>

127
00:08:24,399 --> 00:08:25,589
Okay.

128
00:08:26,519 --> 00:08:28,079
<i>Where are you? I'll pick you up.</i>

129
00:08:28,079 --> 00:08:30,600
I'm not your daughter.

130
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,279
<i>Nan Xi.</i>

131
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:33,320
<i>Dad loves you.</i>

132
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:34,360
<i>It's for your own good.</i>

133
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,675
You're lying.

134
00:08:36,743 --> 00:08:38,280
But it's okay.

135
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,614
I don't love you anymore.

136
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:42,160
No one will ever love me.

137
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:43,679
I will love myself.

138
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,661
<i>You... Nan Xi.</i>

139
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,745
Your hand.

140
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,760
Look, it's much bigger.

141
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,120
Are you crazy?

142
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:39,280
Why did you hit me?

143
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:41,365
Because I have princess syndrome.

144
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,901
Put on a show with me.

145
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,754
What?

146
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,279
Make her come back,

147
00:09:56,279 --> 00:09:58,433
or you'll be sued!

148
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:02,665
Auntie, here you are.

149
00:10:02,665 --> 00:10:03,693
That's enough.

150
00:10:03,693 --> 00:10:05,080
With so many guests,

151
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,720
it's embarrassing if it gets out of hand.

152
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,960
- Back home...
- This is...

153
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,360
He is...

154
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,638
- Well, he...
- Hello.

155
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,640
I'm Nan Xi's lover.

156
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:14,684
You...

157
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:17,720
Mr. Li wants Lu Group's investment.

158
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,399
He forced her to marry into the Lus.

159
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:21,200
But Nan Xi and I are in love.

160
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,079
I hope you can grant our wish.

161
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,840
A gentleman doesn't take
what others like, right?

162
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,840
Sure.

163
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,480
- How could you...
- Mom,

164
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,596
forget it.

165
00:10:41,287 --> 00:10:42,600
I told you,

166
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,280
love cannot be forced.

167
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,320
What did Mr. Li say?

168
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,773
Whatever.

169
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,593
You're right.

170
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,569
Actually...

171
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,098
I want to focus on my career.

172
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:04,998
I'm out.

173
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,479
Stop!

174
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:19,960
Thank you for acting with me.

175
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,200
It's nothing.

176
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,660
Good. We edged out.

177
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:42,120
[Closed]
[Nice to Meet You]

178
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,307
Thank you.

179
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,573
Let's go.

180
00:11:56,698 --> 00:11:58,000
- Nan Feng, Qiao Fei!
- Tian Xiao!

181
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,785
- Come! Come on out!
- Come for a photo!

182
00:11:59,785 --> 00:12:01,960
- Coming!
- Coming! Coming!

183
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,039
- Coming!
- Come, sit with me.

184
00:12:03,039 --> 00:12:04,519
Here, here. Look at the camera!

185
00:12:04,519 --> 00:12:06,120
- Nan Xi, sit here.
- Auntie Ren, you're so pretty!

186
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,600
- Let's start!
- Soon.

187
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,341
Qiao Fei and I will stand behind.

188
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:15,080
Three, two, one!

189
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,208
Cheese!

190
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,360
Okay. Let's go! Let's go inside.

191
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,879
- Okay!
- Let's go!

192
00:12:23,879 --> 00:12:25,088
Let's go!

193
00:12:26,399 --> 00:12:28,274
Let's go. Slowly.

194
00:12:33,213 --> 00:12:36,080
[Closed]

195
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:38,280
Come and try my dish.

196
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:39,960
- Thank you, Auntie Ren!
- You must be starving!

197
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:42,320
- Thank you, Auntie!
- You make the best dishes!

198
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,880
What are you drinking?

199
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,640
- This.
- You have good taste!

200
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,120
You're drinking real natural mineral water.

201
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,569
You earned a lot?

202
00:12:49,569 --> 00:12:50,462
Sure.

203
00:12:50,462 --> 00:12:51,280
- Auntie.
- Thank you.

204
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:54,172
Did He Man Ni agree to
promote you to supervisor?

205
00:12:54,172 --> 00:12:56,559
She called me and asked me to return.

206
00:12:56,559 --> 00:12:58,600
She fired the two useless guys.

207
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:00,559
But... I didn't accept.

208
00:13:00,559 --> 00:13:02,039
You want to stay?

209
00:13:02,039 --> 00:13:03,080
Here.

210
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,600
The diner is doing well.

211
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:08,040
I want to explore the world when I'm young.

212
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:10,639
- It tastes good.
- You want a long-distance relationship?

213
00:13:10,639 --> 00:13:12,607
It's your first love.

214
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,240
You're a good cook.

215
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,639
Actually...

216
00:13:15,639 --> 00:13:17,120
not my first love.

217
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,830
Not your first love?

218
00:13:18,830 --> 00:13:20,185
What?

219
00:13:25,384 --> 00:13:27,785
Oh, I remember now.

220
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:30,000
Don't just ask me. What about you?

221
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,200
Me?

222
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:34,640
I interviewed for an art studio in Yunnan.

223
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:37,320
I can tour, live, and work there.

224
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,639
And the studio

225
00:13:38,639 --> 00:13:41,519
has a whole wall of fish tanks.

226
00:13:41,519 --> 00:13:42,559
Congrats.

227
00:13:42,559 --> 00:13:43,920
You can swim as much as you want.

228
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:44,925
Sure.

229
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:48,600
Don't. I should serve you.

230
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,840
I was wrong.

231
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:52,320
Thank you.

232
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,120
Why are you mentioning it?

233
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,720
When I auditioned that day,

234
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,400
I asked Mr. Chen why I was

235
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,640
called for an audition.

236
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:02,600
He said the female lead, Ms. Jiang,
recommended me,

237
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,799
because a scriptwriter

238
00:14:03,799 --> 00:14:05,799
thought I was good.

239
00:14:05,799 --> 00:14:06,879
I thought it's...

240
00:14:06,879 --> 00:14:08,519
You got it by yourself.

241
00:14:10,039 --> 00:14:12,027
Congrats on getting the role.

242
00:14:12,919 --> 00:14:14,039
Congrats

243
00:14:14,039 --> 00:14:16,832
on becoming a superstar.

244
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:34,759
You haven't told me the city.

245
00:14:34,759 --> 00:14:36,480
But someone said

246
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:39,638
he didn't want to follow me around.

247
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:43,240
Just for inspiration in another city.

248
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,817
Is your work done?

249
00:14:45,879 --> 00:14:48,785
Your script needs an ending.

250
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:50,697
It's done.

251
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,877
What's it like?

252
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,338
Ren Xi Zhou.

253
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:08,810
What?

254
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:12,840
Is it over?

255
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:14,255
Like a dream.

256
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,665
Can we...

257
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,479
No.

258
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,291
Why not?

259
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:23,399
A sweet dream has an end,

260
00:15:23,399 --> 00:15:26,240
just like the rising and falling tides.

261
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:28,360
I won't let it end.

262
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,120
But it's a dream,

263
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,515
understand?

264
00:15:40,351 --> 00:15:41,600
We can still be friends.

265
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,446
Who wants to be your friend?

266
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,865
Why are you going back?

267
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,000
If you don't talk to me,

268
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,710
I'll ignore you forever.

269
00:15:56,159 --> 00:15:58,186
To irrigate my mustard greens.

270
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:03,058
Idiot. Who'd grow mustard greens in summer?

271
00:16:07,376 --> 00:16:08,559
Even if mustard greens

272
00:16:08,559 --> 00:16:09,880
don't taste good in hot days,

273
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:11,902
someone would grow them.

274
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,234
I don't care if it tastes good.

275
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,880
Oh yes,

276
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:26,240
I need to irrigate the mustard greens.

277
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,659
Few people grow mustard greens in summer.
